Rating: 1
I'd have to say this recipe is pretty far off. Perhaps it is pho-inspired, but it isn't the real thing. Rice noodles, first of all, are the right noodles to use. Of course, it's always better if you make the broth from real beef bones or oxtail (note that oxtail adds great flavor, but the broth gets cloudy and stewy). But if you can't, you should at least have the right spices. Too many cloves will make it taste like pumpkin pie pho. I think you also need a stick of cinnamon and some cardomom pods, and more fish sauce. Also, roasting the onions and ginger first intensify the flavors (just put them over the gas flame on the stove like roasting a pepper). Finally, chicken pho is also very good, but the broth is made from chicken, not beef. That's a separate science altogether.

