Rating: 0
I have not tried this recipe, but I am Vietnamese and we do NOT add sliced lettuce in the traditional soup, called pho. We do add a handful of bean sprouts, mint leaves, cilantro leaves and lime juice. Some people add a teaspoon of hoisin sauce and some hot sauce. Add the vegetables when the soup is still very hot and mix it up, so that the heat blances the bean sprouts. Another suggestion is to put some hoisin sauce on the side, for the kids to dip their meat in.

